The Enhanced Pericles and Pericles Vanguard are not available for purchase.  Both are available as [[ownerless ships]].  The Pericles Vanguard is also available [[Buy Used Ship|used]], and the Enhanced Pericles is granted by [[Duke's|Duke's Buccaneers]] upon reaching [[Reputation#Duke's|rank 4]].

In AP, the Enhanced Pericles is available for purchase in some Paranid shipyards.

== Suggested Roles==
The Pericles' inability to carry M-class cargo prevents it from mounting a [[jumpdrive]], which limits its utility as a fighter to carrier-based and station-defense applications.  Also limiting it is a weapons selection no better than the [[Demeter]] and [[Hermes]] freighters. Further adding to the drawbacks of this interceptor is its inability to carry [[fighter drone]]s, as they're M-class cargo and the Pericles' aforementioned S-class cargo limitation makes it weak for its class.

